# LaunchLook standing instructions

Read `docs/LESSONS-LEARNED.md` for the full rationale. These are the directives.

---

## Canonical numbers — never substitute your own

Always grep `scripts/launchlook_constants.py` and `docs/PRODUCT-DECISIONS.md §1` first.

| Value | Canonical |
|---|---|
| Free tier delivery | **2 findings** (`FREE_AUDIT_DELIVER_COUNT = 2`) |
| Free tier pipeline depth | Starter cap (10) — runs at 10, delivers top 2 |
| Starter Package ($19) | Up to **10** findings |
| Scale Up Package ($49) | Up to **30** findings |
| Pro Package ($99) | Up to **40** findings |
| Tier count | Hard cap at **4**: Free / Starter / Scale Up / Pro |
| Tester personas | Hard cap at **7**: never add an 8th |
| Refund window | **7 days** |
| Free → Starter dedup | **90 days** |
| Handoff Report add-on | **$49** (not $99) |
| Fix Check standalone / discounted | **$19** / **$9 within 14 days** |

When a number appears in both code and customer-facing copy, add a drift test in `tests/`.

