## Brand voice — hard rules

**Read `docs/SIMPLICITY-GUARDRAILS.md` before touching any customer surface.**

Never on any customer-facing surface:
- ❌ Em-dashes (exception: `— Rob` email sign-off only)
- ❌ "Trust Gaps" → ✅ "embarrassing bugs"
- ❌ "native apps" → ✅ "desktop and mobile width testing"
- ❌ "AI-powered scanner," "automation," "intelligent analysis," "next-generation"
- ❌ "leverage," "utilize," "seamless," "robust," "elevate," "empower," "unlock," "supercharge," "revolutionize," "best-in-class," "world-class," "cutting-edge," "streamline," "powerful"
- ❌ "advanced," "premium," "professional" (we have a Pro tier; don't repeat the word)
- ❌ Internal taxonomy on customer surfaces: "Snoop," "fingerprint dedup," "Scale-Ready," "AI pipeline," "Compliance-Lite," "axe-core," "Core Web Vitals"
- ❌ Technical jargon in finding titles (allowed only in fix prompt blocks per §3.1)
- ❌ 5th tier, 8th Tester persona, or anything from `PRODUCT-DECISIONS.md §3` (killed list)

Voice check: Would a non-technical vibe-coder founder understand this in under 5 seconds? Every sentence under 20 words? Second person active?

---

## LLM prompts for tiered products

Use target ranges with explicit minimums, not just ceilings:
- Starter: target 5-10 (cap 10)
- Scale Up: **target 20-30, minimum 20** — walk every finding category
- Pro: **target 30-40, minimum 30** — walk every category + integrations

Always pair with anti-padding guardrail:
> "You may NOT invent findings to pad the count. If a category truly does not apply, skip it."

See `scripts/ai_audit/pipeline.py` `_tier_guidance()`.

---

## UI defaults

- Status messages and microcopy under CTAs: **always `text-center`**
- URL inputs: **accept bare hostnames** (`mysite.com`) — normalize client AND server
- Footer: **Rob's personal card** — name, 1-line bio, email, LinkedIn — nothing else, no duplicate email links on same page

---

## Email notifications

- Always send **multipart HTML + text** via Resend (`html` + `text` fields)
- Long mailto URLs go inside `<a href="...">` in HTML — never in plain-text bodies
- Plain-text fallback uses a compact subject-only mailto (no `?body=...`)
- Set `User-Agent: LaunchLook-Automation/1.0 (+https://launchlook.app)` on every outbound API call (Cloudflare WAF blocks `Python-urllib/X.Y`)
- Resend `FROM_EMAIL` must be a domain verified in Resend (`launchlook.app` is already verified)

---

## Workflow: clickable links beat CLI commands

If a workflow step can be a link, make it a link. Founder emails include:
- `http://localhost:8000/review/<slug>` — AI review editor
- `http://localhost:8000/preview/<slug>` — live report preview
- `mailto:` button — pre-composed delivery draft

CLI commands appear only as fallbacks when the review server isn't running.

**Customer delivery is always manual.** Never call `deliver_report.py --send` automatically. The human gate is non-negotiable.

---

## Before every push

```powershell
python -m ruff check <changed-files>     # specific paths, not .
python -m ruff format <changed-files>    # specific paths, not .
python -m pytest tests/ -x -q
```

All three green or don't push. Running `ruff format .` on the whole repo creates noise in unrelated files.

---

## Shell is PowerShell

- ❌ `cmd1 && cmd2` → ✅ `cmd1; if ($?) { cmd2 }`
- ❌ Heredocs (`<<EOF`) → ✅ here-strings (`@"..."@`) or `git commit -F file.txt`
- ❌ `ruff check` → ✅ `python -m ruff check`
- ❌ Unicode in `print()` without `$env:PYTHONIOENCODING="utf-8"`
- Flask stderr in PowerShell shows as `NativeCommandError` even on exit 0 — smoke-check with HTTP request, not by reading stderr

---

## Vercel Python serverless

`api/*.py` must be self-contained. Never import from `scripts/`. Inline constants and add a drift test:

```python
# In api/free-audit.py — inlined intentionally
FREE_AUDIT_DELIVER_COUNT = 2  # enforced by tests/test_launchlook_constants.py
```

`FUNCTION_INVOCATION_FAILED` at cold start = top-level import didn't bundle.

---

## Commit messages

Pattern: `scope: one-line present-tense summary`

Examples:
- `fix(audit): make tier guidance target minimums so Pro audits hit ~30-40 findings`
- `landing: center status + disclaimer text under submit button`
- `trust: add IP-theft FAQ + pricing trust note`

Cite `SIMPLICITY-GUARDRAILS.md` rule numbers (e.g. `§2.1`) when making brand judgment calls.

---

## Notion property normalization

Normalize at the boundary with a lookup dict. Never use a silent fallback (`.get(key, 7)`). Always log WARN when an unrecognised value hits the fallback.

```python
TIER_NORMALIZE = {
    "pro package": "Pro Package",
    "pro package ($99)": "Pro Package",
    "pro": "Pro Package",
    ...
}
```

